@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Twinine" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Twinine runs
      fine on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga
      with a 68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  The game board consists of 64 tiles where each tile is occupied
by two twine portions, one is white and the other black. To play,
click on any tile, this will make the twine portions rotate
clockwise by 90 degrees.

  To make a complete twine, all parts of the twine must be
'connected' with neighbouring parts of the same colour; either in
black or white (or whatever colour you use as colour 1 and 2 on
your Workbench palette). Each completed twine must start at the
upper left and end at the lower right position on the board. Also,
the first and last twine portions must be connected to the game
board's edge. When both black and white twines are completed, all
the connected twine parts will be shown in colour, then, the game
will display a new board...

  The idea is to make the longest twines by using as many twine
parts as possible, because the game keeps the highest combined
number of parts for both twines...

  Have fun!

  You can restart the game by clicking on the 'New Game' button.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

